Elizabeth (Liz) Rihl Lewinsky joins Tuition Exchange as Associate Vice President for Member Engagement

Selected from a pool of over 170 highly qualified candidates as part of a national search, Elizabeth (“Liz”) Rihl Lewinsky is joining the Tuition Exchange as Associate Vice President for Member Engagement. Liz brings over 30 years of experience in Financial Aid and Enrollment Management, including extensive experience as a Tuition Exchange Liaison Officer at multiple institutions and has administered TE, CIC and . . .

Continuing Tuition Exchange Scholars' Application Status

Current Tuition Exchange Scholarship recipients who are continuing at the same institution do not need to re-submit the TE EZ-Application each year. Continuing students must check with the EXPORT school to determine if additional paperwork is required. A new TE EZ-Application should only be submitted if your student is considering transferring to a new Tuition Exchange school. Students who wish to transfer . . .

How to check my NEW TE application status

Did you receive an email that the status of your NEW Tuition Exchange application changed? Are you just curious as to the status of your NEW Tuition Exchange applications? It is easy to check provided you have the correct student information. If you are unable to access you need to contact your EXPORT TE Liaison Officer for the information provided on your EZ application or the information you provided to your Export TE . . .
